# UI Design Guidelines

## Main Window Layout
- **Image Display Area**: Central canvas for image viewing and annotation
- **Toolbar**: Buttons for navigation, class selection, and actions
- **Status Bar**: Display current image info, coordinates, and instructions
- **File Browser**: Optional sidebar for image navigation

## Bounding Box Interaction
- **Mouse Events**:
  - Click and drag to create rectangles
  - Click on existing boxes to select/edit
  - Right-click for context menu (delete, change class)
- **Visual Feedback**:
  - Highlight selected bounding box
  - Show coordinates during drag operations
  - Different colors for different classes

## Navigation Controls
- **Previous/Next Image**: Arrow keys or buttons
- **Zoom**: Mouse wheel or zoom controls
- **Pan**: Drag when zoomed in
- **Fit to Window**: Auto-resize image to fit display

## Class Management
- **Class Selection**: Dropdown or button group
- **Add New Class**: Dialog for creating new classes
- **Class Colors**: Assign distinct colors to each class
- **Class Statistics**: Show count of annotations per class

## Keyboard Shortcuts
- `Space`: Next image
- `Backspace`: Previous image
- `Delete`: Remove selected bounding box
- `Ctrl+S`: Save annotations
- `Ctrl+Z`: Undo last action
- `Escape`: Cancel current operation

## Error Handling
- Display user-friendly error messages
- Validate image file formats
- Handle corrupted or missing files gracefully
- Provide feedback for save operations